TotalGoals <- matches.premierLeague$match_hometeam_score + matches.premierLeague$match_awayteam_score

# to add the total goals to the table 

matches.premierLeague <- cbind(matches.premierLeague, TotalGoals)

hist(matches.premierLeague$TotalGoals, main="Total Match Goals ",xlab="Match Goals", ylab="Frequency",xlim=c(-1,10))

Home_Goals_min_AwayGoals <- matches.premierLeague$match_hometeam_score - matches.premierLeague$match_awayteam_score

# to add the home goals  away goals to the table 

matches.premierLeague <- cbind(matches.premierLeague, Home_Goals_min_AwayGoals)

hist(matches.premierLeague$Home_Goals_min_AwayGoals, main="Difference of Goals ",xlab="Difference of Goals home-Away", ylab="Frequency",xlim=c(-10,10))

# Home_goal_sum
Home_goal_sum <- sum(matches.premierLeague$match_hometeam_score)
print("Home_goal_sum = ")
## [1] "Home_goal_sum = "
Home_goal_sum
## [1] 990
# No of matches.premierLeague
print("No_of_matches.premierLeague = ")
## [1] "No_of_matches.premierLeague = "
#No_of_matches.premierLeague
No_of_matches.premierLeague <- nrow(matches.premierLeague)
# to calculate lambda of the poisson dist of home team goals
Lamda_home_goal <- Home_goal_sum / No_of_matches.premierLeague
print("Lambda of poisson of home team goals = ")
## [1] "Lambda of poisson of home team goals = "
Lamda_home_goal
## [1] 1.601942
# to draw the poisson dist with  lambda (home team)
curve (dpois(x, lambda= Lamda_home_goal),xlim=c(0,8),n=9)

print(" CONCLUSION Home team goals distribution looks like poisson")
## [1] " CONCLUSION Home team goals distribution looks like poisson"
# to sum up Away_goals in the premier league
Away_goal_sum <- sum(matches.premierLeague$match_awayteam_score)
print("Away_goal_sum = ")
## [1] "Away_goal_sum = "
Away_goal_sum
## [1] 759
# No of matches.premierLeague
print("No_of_matches.premierLeague = ")
## [1] "No_of_matches.premierLeague = "
No_of_matches.premierLeague
## [1] 618
No_of_matches.premierLeague <- nrow(matches.premierLeague)
#to calculate lambda of the poisson dist of away team goals
Lamda_away_goal <- Away_goal_sum / No_of_matches.premierLeague
print("Lambda of poisson of away team goals = ")

Lamda_away_goal

print(" CONCLUSION Away team goals distribution looks like poisson")

#fix (task_2_matches.premierLeague_bets1_odds1_2_x_odd_bookmakers_bwin)

# to normalize probabilities of odd_bookmakers 1xBet
#library(data.table)
#library(dplyr) x

#fix (task_2_matches.premierLeague_bets1_odds1_2_x_odd_bookmakers_1xBet)
setDT(task_2_matches.premierLeague_bets1_odds1_2_x_odd_bookmakers_1xBet)
normalized_prob_of_1xBet <-dcast(task_2_matches.premierLeague_bets1_odds1_2_x_odd_bookmakers_1xBet,  match_id + odd_bookmakers + odd_epoch  ~  variable,  value.var  = "value")

#fix(normalized_prob_of_1xBet )

# to odd probabilities

probability_odds_1  <- (1 / normalized_prob_of_1xBet$odd_1)
probability_odds_2  <- (1 / normalized_prob_of_1xBet$odd_2)
probability_odds_x  <- (1 / normalized_prob_of_1xBet$odd_x)

sum_probability_odds <- (probability_odds_1  +  probability_odds_2  + probability_odds_x  )

# to normalize probabilities

normalized_probability_odds_1 <- (probability_odds_1  / sum_probability_odds)
normalized_probability_odds_2 <- (probability_odds_2  / sum_probability_odds)
normalized_probability_odds_x <- (probability_odds_x  / sum_probability_odds)

# to calculate  P(home)  P(away)

normalized_probability_odds_1_minus_odds_2 <- normalized_probability_odds_1 - normalized_probability_odds_2

# to sum of normalized probabilities =1
sum_normalized_probability <- (normalized_probability_odds_1 + normalized_probability_odds_2 + normalized_probability_odds_x)

# to add all the probabilities to data

normalized_prob_of_1xBet <- cbind (normalized_prob_of_1xBet, probability_odds_1, probability_odds_2  , probability_odds_x, sum_probability_odds, normalized_probability_odds_1, normalized_probability_odds_2, normalized_probability_odds_x, sum_normalized_probability, normalized_probability_odds_1_minus_odds_2)

#fix(normalized_prob_of_1xBet )

normalized_prob_of_1xBet$binx <- cut(normalized_prob_of_1xBet$normalized_probability_odds_1_minus_odds_2, breaks = seq (-1,1,0.2))

normalized_prob_of_1xBet$biny <- cut(normalized_prob_of_1xBet$normalized_probability_odds_x, breaks = seq (0,1,0.2))


plot(normalized_prob_of_1xBet$binx, normalized_prob_of_1xBet$biny)
